iden-budget-proposal-child-tax-credit-social-security-taxing-rich-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBiden's%20tax%20priorities%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20he%20secure%20a%20second%20term.%20They're%20largely%20focused%20on%20ensuring%20big%20corporations%20and%20the%20wealthy%20pay%20what%20Biden%20deems%20their%20fair%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20White%20House's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2024%2F03%2F07%2Ffact-sheet-president-biden-is-fighting-to-reduce-the-deficit-cut-taxes-for-working-families-and-invest-in-america-by-making-big-corporations-and-the-wealthy-pay-their-fair-share%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efact%20sheet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Biden's%20tax%20plan%20would%20seek%20to%20raise%20the%20corporate%20tax%20rate%20from%2021%25%20to%2028%25%2C%20and%20the%20minimum%20corporate%20tax%20rate%20from%2015%25%20to%2021%25.%20This%20differs%20from%20Trump's%20tax%20plan%3A%20His%202017%20Tax%20Cuts%20and%20Jobs%20Act%20established%20a%2021%25%20corporate%20income%20tax%20rate%20%E2%80%94%20a%20decrease%20from%2035%25%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Trump%20would%20maintain%20that%20rate%2C%20Bloomberg%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-01-06%2Ftrump-considers-making-2017-personal-tax-cuts-permanent%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Biden%20wants%20to%20require%20billionaires%20%E2%80%94%20the%20richest%200.01%25%2C%20or%20people%20worth%20%24100%20million%20or%20more%20%E2%80%94%20to%20pay%20at%20least%2025%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20taxes%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20said%20that%20Biden's%20tax%20plan%20would%20cut%20taxes%20for%20middle-%20and%20low-income%20people%20by%20%24765%20billion%20over%2010%20years.%20This%20would%20be%20accomplished%20by%20restoring%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fenhanced-child-tax-credit-parents-passes-house-business-tax-relief-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efully%20refundable%20expanded%20child-tax%20credit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20first%20enacted%20under%20the%20American%20Rescue%20Plan%20in%202021%20and%20gave%20%243%2C000%20per%20child%20to%20families%20with%20children%20over%20the%20age%20of%206%2C%20and%20%243%2C600%20per%20child%20to%20families%20with%20children%20under%20the%20age%20of%206.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden%20would%20also%20increase%20the%20Earned%20Income%20Tax%20Credit%2C%20which%20is%20a%20refundable%20tax%20credit%20for%20working%20individuals%20or%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Trump%20has%20not%20yet%20released%20a%20detailed%20tax%20plan%2C%20many%20of%20the%20provisions%20in%20his%202017%20tax%20law%20are%20set%20to%20expire%20in%202025.%20Biden's%20tax%20plan%20would%20support%20extending%20Trump's%20tax%20cuts%20for%20households%20making%20under%20%24400%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20but%20some%20Republican%20lawmakers%20want%20all%20of%20Trump's%20provisions%20extended%20past%202025%2C%20and%20they%20introduced%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F118th-congress%2Fhouse-bill%2F976%3Fs%3D1%26r%3D68%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebill%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%20to%20make%20the%20tax%20law%20permanent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20also%20proposed%20a%2010%25%20tariff%20on%20goods%20coming%20into%20the%20US%2C%20along%20with%20a%2060%25%20tariff%20on%20all%20imports%20from%20China.%20The%20Tax%20Foundation%2C%20a%20nonpartisan%20think%20tank%2C%20has%20said%20the%20proposed%2010%25%20tariff%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftaxfoundation.org%2Fblog%2Fdonald-trump-10-percent-tariff%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewould%20raise%20taxes%20for%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20over%20%24300%20billion%20a%20year.%20Trump%20recently%20said%20during%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F6972022%2Fdonald-trump-transcript-2024-election%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_bla