20few%20weeks%20into%20his%20search%2C%20however%2C%20Holbrook%20found%20himself%20out%20of%20his%20depth.%20Instead%20of%20speaking%20with%20a%20human%20recruiter%20at%20a%20local%20healthcare%20organization%2C%20he%20was%20screened%20by%20an%20AI%20chatbot.%20His%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20created%20nearly%20a%20decade%20ago%20in%20a%20technical%20format%20popular%20among%20academics%2C%20was%20incompatible%20with%20new%20automated%20recruitment%20platforms.%20He%20signed%20up%20for%20a%20professional%20service%20to%20update%20it%20in%20an%20AI-friendly%20format.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20experience%20was%20completely%20novel%2C%26quot%3B%20Holbrook%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BI've%20never%20seen%20that%20before.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-market-high-pay-employees-labor-economy-finding-work-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20seekers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20contend%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-firings-tech-hr-tiktok-cloudflare-employee-morale-bad-business-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincessant%20layoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatgpt-hiring-ghost-interviews-job-search-weird-labor-market-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrutal%20recruitment%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20days%20of%20unpaid%20assignments.%20They%20can%20now%20add%20AI%20recruiting%20systems%20to%20that%20pile.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20Society%20for%20Human%20Resource%20Management%20found%20that%20about%2040%25%20of%20the%20large-scale%20employers%20it%20surveyed%20said%20they%20were%20already%20deploying%20AI%20in%20HR-related%20activities%20like%20recruitment.%20Rik%20Mistry%2C%20who%20consults%20on%20large-scale%20corporate%20recruitment%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20AI%20is%20now%20leveraged%20to%20write%20job%20descriptions%2C%20judge%20an%20applicant's%20skills%2C%20power%20recruiting%20chatbots%2C%20and%20rate%20a%20candidate's%20responses.%20Ian%20Siegel%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20ZipRecruiter%2C%20estimated%20in%202022%20that%20nearly%20three-fourths%20of%20all%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20were%20never%20seen%20by%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20job%20hunters%20have%20decided%20to%20fight%20fire%20with%20fire%2C%20turning%20to%20programs%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-applications-hiring-ai-bots-spam-resume-cover-letter-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euse%20AI%20to%20optimize%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20apply%20to%20hundreds%20of%20jobs%20at%20a%20time.%20But%20the%20emerging%20AI-versus-AI%20recruitment%20battle%20is%20bad%20news%20for%20everyone.%20It%20turns%20hiring%20into%20a%20depersonalized%20process%2C%20it%20inundates%20hiring%20managers%2C%20and%20it%20reinforces%20weaknesses%20in%20the%20system%20it's%20designed%20to%20improve.%20And%20it%20only%20seems%20to%20be%20getting%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAutomation%20in%20recruitment%20isn't%20new%3A%20After%20job%20sites%20like%20Monster%20and%20LinkedIn%20made%20it%20easy%20for%20people%20to%20apply%20for%20jobs%20in%20the%20early%202010s%2C%20companies%20adopted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-your-resume-gets-rejected-job-search-bots-people-ats-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapplicant-tracking%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20manage%20the%20deluge%20of%20online%20applications.%20Now%20most%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20are%20first%20seen%20by%20software%20designed%20to%20evaluate%20a%20person's%20experience%20and%20education%20and%20rank%20them%20accordingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20automation%20has%20helped%20ease%20the%20burden%20on%20overstretched%20recruiters%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20by%20much.%20As%20the%20stacks%20of%20digital%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20have%20grown%20amid%20frequent%20changes%20to%20remote-work%20policies%2C%20the%20recruitment%20hamster%20wheel%20has%20spun%20ever%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20is%20supposed%20to%20fix%20this%20mess%2C%20saving%20companies%20time%20and%20money%20by%20outsourcing%20even%20more%20of%20the%20hiring%20process%20to%20machine-learning%20algorithms.%20In%20late%202019%2C%20Unilever%20said%20it%20had%20saved%20100%2C000%20hours%20and%20about%20%241%20million%20in%20recruitment%20costs%20with%20the%20help%20of%20automated%20video%20interviews.%20Platforms%20like%20LinkedIn%20and%20ZipRecruiter%20have%20started%20using%20generative%20AI%20to%20offer%20candidates%20personalized%20job%20recommendations%20and%20let%20recruiters%20generate%20listings%20in%20seconds.%20The%20Google-backed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoonhub-secures-1-4-million-for-vr-training-platform-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecruitment-tech%20startup%20Moonhub%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20an%20AI%20bot%20that%20scours%20the%20internet%2C%20gathering%20data%20from%20places%20like%20LinkedIn%20and%20Github%2C%20to%20find%20suitable%20candidates.%20On%20HireVue%2C%20employers%20can%20let%20a%20bot%20with%20a%20set%20questionnaire%20conduct%20video%20assessments%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-surveillance-detects-emotion-at-work-gets-you-fired-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20analyze%20candidates'%20personalities%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Newer%20startups%20combine%20these%20abilities%20in%20a%20centralized%20service%2C%20allowing%20firms%20to%20put%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fhollyhires.ai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehiring%20on%20autopilot%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20hiring%20experts%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20weren't%20convinced%20it's%20all%20for%20the%20best.%20Many%20fear%20that%20over%20time%20AI%20will%20make%20an%20already%20frustrating%20system%20worse%20and%20spawn%20fresh%20issues%20like%20ghost%20hires%2C%20where%20companies%20are%20misled%20into%20recruiting%20a%20bot%20masquerading%20as%20a%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20seasoned%20recruiters%20told%20me%20they%20hadn't%20incorporated%20AI%20into%20their%20workflow%20beyond%20auto-generating%20job%20descriptions%20and%20summarizing%20candidate%20calls.%20Tatiana%20Becker%2C%20who%20specializes%20in%20tech%20recruiting%2C%20said%20software%20that%20claims%20to%20match%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20with%20jobs%20lacked%20the%20nuance%20to%20do%20more%20than%20keyword%20matching%20%E2%80%94%20it%20couldn't%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20identify%20desirable%20candidates%20who%20came%20from%20top%20schools%20or%20had%20a%20history%20of%20earning%20strong%20promotions.%20Chatbots%20that%20Becker's%20boutique%20agency%20experimented%20with%20would%20frequently%20mismatch%20prospects%20and%20roles%2C%20ultimately%20pushing%20the%20prospects%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20matching%20%26quot%3Bmight%20work%20for%20applicants%20of%20more%20entry-level%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20Becker%20told%20BI%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20I%20would%20worry%20about%20using%20it%20for%20anything%20else%20at%20this%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20problems%2C%20many%20companies%20are%20marching%20forward.%20%26quot%3BWe%20know%20AI%20isn't%20perfect%2C%20but%20we%20have%20to%20use%20it%20as%20there's%20pressure%20from%20the%20higher-ups%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20recruiter%20in%20a%20Fortune%20500%20firm%20who%20spoke%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20to%20candidly%20discuss%20his%20company's%20hiring%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPallavi%20Sinha%2C%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20growth%20at%20Humanly%2C%20a%20startup%20that%20offers%20a%20conversational-AI%20hiring%20platform%20to%20companies%20like%20Microsoft%2C%20said%20that%20%26quot%3BAI%20in%20recruiting%2C%20similar%20to%20other%20industries%2C%20is%20very%20much%20at%20a%20nascent%20stage.%26quot%3B%20But%20she%20predicted%20it%20would%20continue%20to%20be%20incorporated%20into%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20isn't%20here%20to%20replace%20human%20interactions%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20to%20make%20our%20jobs%20and%20lives%20easier%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20we'll%20see%20more%20and%20more%20of%20over%20time.%26quot%3B%20Sinha%20declined%20to%20share%20how%20many%20applications%20Humanly%20had%20processed%20but%20said%20its%20chatbot%20service%20had%20over%20a%20%26quot%3Bmillion%20conversations%20last%20year%20alone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20candidates%2C%20though%2C%20AI%20has%20been%20a%20nightmare.%20Kerry%20McInerney%2C%20an%20AI%20researcher%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge%2C%20said%20AI%20increases%20the%20amount%20of%20labor%20for%20applicants%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20complete%20puzzles%20and%20attend%20automated%20interviews%20just%20to%20get%20to%20the%20selection%20stage.%20She%20argued%20that%20it%20makes%20a%20%26quot%3Bdepersonalized%20process%20even%20more%20alienating.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHolbrook%2C%20the%20software%20engineer%2C%20wrote%20on%20LinkedIn%20about%20his%20frustration.%20%26quot%3BAI%20is%20too%20stupid%20to%20recognize%20transferrable%20skills%20among%20tech%20applicants%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20a%20resume%20bounced%20because%20I%20don't%20have%20c%23%20listed%20as%20a%20fluent%20language%2C%20even%20though%20I've%20dealt%20with%20c%23%20in%20my%20jobs%20and%20have%20worked%20with%20plenty%20of%20languages%20that%20are%2090%25%20the%20same%20as%20c%23.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanielle%20Caldwell%2C%20a%20user-experience%20strategist%20in%20Portland%2C%20Oregon%2C%20was%20confused%20when%20an%20AI%20chatbot%20texted%20her%20to%20initiate%20the%20conversation%20about%20a%20role%20she%20had%20applied%20for.%20At%20first%2C%20she%20thought%20it%20was%20spam.%20After%20the%20exchange%2C%20she%20was%20left%20with%20more%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20way%20to%20ask%20questions%20with%20the%20bot%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20a%20one-way%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20Caldwell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20University%20of%20Sussex%20has%20found%20that%20AI%20video%20interviews%20can%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.sussex.ac.uk%2Fpolicy-engagement%2Ffiles%2F2021%2F10%2FAutomated-job-interviews-and-the-implications-for-young-jobseekers.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisorienting%20for%20job%20seekers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20behave%20much%20less%20naturally%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20reassuring%20human%20presence.%20Plus%2C%20Mclnerney%20said%2C%20assessing%20a%20candidate's%20personality%20based%20on%20their%20body%20language%20and%20appearance%20is%20not%20only%20%26quot%3Breminiscent%20of%2019th-%20and%2020th-century%20racial%20pseudoscience%20but%20simply%20doesn't%20work.%26quot%3B%20Her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs13347-022-00543-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20demonstrated%20that%20even%20things%20like%20wearing%20a%20headscarf%20or%20having%20a%20bookshelf%20in%20the%20background%20can%20change%20a%20personality%20score.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20cottage%20industry%20of%20tools%20has%20sprung%20up%20to%20help%20candidates%20game%20AI%20systems.%20One%20called%20LazyApply%2C%20for%20example%2C%20can%20apply%20to%20thousands%20of%20jobs%20online%20on%20your%20behalf%20for%20%24250.%20%26quot%3BAnyone%20who%20has%20had%20to%20review%20over%2050%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20in%20one%20sitting%20wants%20to%20put%20a%20toothpick%20in%20their%20eyes%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Peter%20Laughter%2C%20who's%20been%20in%20recruitment%20for%20about%20three%20decades.%20With%20AI%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20are%20only%20accelerating%20the%20brokenness%20of%20recruiting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBonnie%20Dilber%2C%20a%20recruiting%20manager%20at%20Zapier%2C%20said%20these%20services%20contributed%20to%20problematic%20behaviors%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20hiring.%20Candidates'%20submitting%20hundreds%20of%20applications%20leaves%20recruiting%20teams%20struggling%20to%20keep%20up%20and%20respond%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20pushes%20applicants%20to%20feel%20that%20they%20need%20to%20submit%20even%20more%20applications%20to%20stand%20a%20chance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20more%20pressing%20issue%2C%20Dilber%20added%2C%20is%20that%20often%20these%20bots%20submit%20poor%20applications.%20Dilber%20and%20other%20recruiters%20told%20BI%20that%20some%20cover%20letters%20say%20only%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20has%20been%20submitted%20by%20%5BAI%20tool%5D%2C%20please%20contact%20%5Bperson's%20email%5D%20with%20questions.%26quot%3B%20When%20Aki%20Ito%2C%20a%20BI%20correspondent%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-applications-hiring-ai-bots-spam-resume-cover-letter-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etried%20using%20AI%20to%20apply%20for%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20system%20got%20her%20race%20wrong%2C%20made%20up%20that%20she%20spoke%20Spanish%2C%20and%20submitted%20an%20outdated%20cover%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20some%20people%20accidentally%20include%20ChatGPT's%20entire%20response%2C%26quot%3B%20Hailley%20Griffis%2C%20the%20head%20of%20communications%20and%20content%20at%20Buffer%2C%20told%20BI.%20Griffis%2C%20who%20said%20she%20reviewed%20an%20average%20of%20500%20applications%20per%20open%20role%2C%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20very%20distinct%20tone%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20AI%20content%20that%20hasn't%20been%20edited%2C%20and%20we%20saw%20a%20lot%20of%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ERecruiters%20and%20researchers%20also%20worry%20about%20AI's%20tendency%20to%20reinforce%20many%20of%20the%20recruitment%20industry's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-racism-bias-new-inclusive-solutions-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexisting%20biases%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Researchers%20from%20the%20Berkeley%20Haas%20Center%20for%20Equity%2C%20Gender%20and%20Leadership%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fssir.org%2Farticles%2Fentry%2Fwhen_good_algorithms_go_sexist_why_and_how_to_advance_ai_gender_equity%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20of%20about%20133%20biased%20AI%20systems%20they%20analyzed%2C%20about%2044%25%20exhibited%20gender%20bias.%20Other%20recent%20studies%20have%20found%20that%20AI%20systems%20are%20prone%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffederalnewsnetwork.com%2Fartificial-intelligence%2F2022%2F05%2Feeoc-doj-sounding-alarm-over-ai-hiring-tools-that-screen-out-disabled-applicants%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escreening%20out%20applicants%20with%20disabilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20de-ranking%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20with%20names%20associated%20with%20Black%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20a%20human%2C%20an%20algorithm%20will%20never%20look%20at%20past%20hiring%20decisions%20and%20rectify%20its%20mistakes%2C%20said%20Sandra%20Wachter%2C%20a%20tech%20and%20regulation%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Oxford.%20It%20will%20always%20do%20as%20it%20has%20been%20taught.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWachter%2C%20whose%20team%20developed%20a%20bias%20test%20that's%20been%20adopted%20by%20companies%20like%20IBM%20and%20Amazon%2C%20believes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-help-recruit-hire-employees-tech-women-bias-job-seeking-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit's%20possible%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20make%20fairer%20decisions%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20for%20that%20to%20happen%2C%20employers%20need%20to%20address%20systemic%20issues%20with%20more%20inclusive%20data%20and%20regular%20checks.%20Moonhub%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20a%20human%20recruiter%20who%20vets%20the%20AI's%20recommendations%20and%20speaks%20with%20candidates%20who%20prefer%20a%20human%20over%20a%20chatbot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20until%20AI%20improves%20enough%2C%20humans%20will%20remain%20the%20most%20effective%20hiring%20systems.%20Becker%2C%20the%20tech%20recruiter%2C%20said%20humans%20were%20still%20critical%20for%20%26quot%3Bgetting%20to%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20candidate's%20decision-making%20process%20and%20helping%20them%20overcome%20apprehensions%20if%20they've%20gotten%20cold%20feet%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20well%20as%20for%20%26quot%3Bdealing%20with%20counteroffers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Francis%2C%20a%20vice%20president%20at%20Talent%20Tech%20Labs%2C%20a%20recruitment%20research%20and%20advisory%20firm%2C%20said%20that%20while%20%26quot%3Brecruitment%20is%20still%20and%20will%20always%20be%20a%20very%20human-focused%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20AI%20%26quot%3Bis%20a%20tool%20and%20can%20be%20used%20effectively%20or%20poorly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20it's%20used%20poorly%2C%20both%20candidates%20and%20recruiters%20suffer.%20After%20four%20months%20of%20job%20searching%2C%20Josh%20Holbrook%20has%20yet%20to%20find%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fshubham-agarwal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EShubham%20Agarwal%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20freelance%20technology%20journalist%20from%20Ahmedabad%2C%20India%2C%20whose%20work%20has%20appeared%20in%20Wired%2C%20The%20Verge%2C%20Fast%20Company%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobseekers-recruiters-hiring-broken-ai-bots-resumes-interviews-spam-bias-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715852281000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664224eb9686a6f37bff359c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobseekers-recruiters-hiring-broken-ai-bots-resumes-interviews-spam-bias-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AI%20bots%20are%20battling%20it%20out%20over%20job%20searches.%20No%20matter%20who%20wins%2C%20we%20all%20